description:
Making life a little bit SWEETER, one bar of chocolate at a time üòã

Recently, I‚Äôve been loving these @gatsbychocolate bars, which are made with fresh, crunchy almond bits draped in velvety dark chocolate. I‚Äôm at that age of adulting where I love deeply flavorful and slightly bittersweet dark chocolates, and I love how this one is perfectly sweet and not diluted by the addition of excess milk or sugar. Best of all, each bar contains half the calories and a quarter of the sugar typically found in an average chocolate bar, and is keto-friendly! 

Thank you @gatsbychocolate for sending me so many chocolate bars to try! Definitely make sure to check out their products at your local @ralphsgrocery , whether you‚Äôre looking for an indulgent snack or an essential baking ingredient! #gifted

description:
Was so BERRY excited to finally CHAI out @ateamuseum , and I definitely was not disappointed with how cute their drinks and desserts were! Here are some of my thoughts:

üçì coconut pudding with fresh strawberry: I‚Äôve been seeing this all over IG, and I just HAD to get this dessert! Their coconut pudding is super light and subtly sweet, and topped with a layer of freshly chopped fruits (your choice of mango or strawberry). 

üç† taro with fresh milk: loved how they used real taro paste for this drink, although I wish they used more (since this drink ended up being mostly milk). This drink also uses white boba, which is a healthier alternative to tapioca balls, and has a more light and crunch texture. Definitely recommend if you‚Äôre looking for a non-caffeinated drink!

üêØ brown sugar milk tea: definitely my favorite drink out of the trio, and it‚Äôs absolutely perfectly sweetened and creamy with 50% sweetness and light ice. Their boba is also super chewy and well made, and would definitely recommend adding it as a topping in other drinks! 

üçä super fruit green tea: highly recommend this drink if you want something a bit more natural and fruity! I loved how there were so many fresh fruits in the drink, and how the flavors of each fruit melded beautifully with the fragrance of the green tea. Would recommend getting this at 100% sweetness and light ice since this is a bit lighter in flavor compared to the other drinks!

Thank you @ateamuseum for such a SWEET invite to try out your drinks and desserts! Definitely make sure to check them out at both of their Milpitas and Sunnyvale locations, and support a small, local and Asian-owned business! #invite

Fun fact: I took 3 years of high school and college level French because I wanted to study abroad in France one day. It ended up never happening üòÖ but a girl can dream right? Still hoping to brush up on my rusty French and travel again sometime when it‚Äôs safe in the future. Where‚Äôs your dream destination to travel to?

Thank you @527photo and @stackinfluence for sending me such a lovely collection of 50 Paris-themed prints. Each shot is beautifully edited and printed on matte photo paper (so you don‚Äôt get that glare when you try to look at it). Definitely make sure to check out her prints on @etsy if you‚Äôve been looking for some decor and travel inspo! #gifted #527photo #527photopartner

I might have started Invisalign a few days ago (swipe to see how I look LOL üôàüëÄ), but that sure isn‚Äôt stopping me from digging into this delicious box of Korean snacks from @atcenterla ! Korean snacks are definitely my weakness, and this box was filled with such a yummy variety of both sweet and savory treats! Among my favorites were the lotte milk candies, milkis, drinkable peach jelly, and all the spicy instant noodles, which I absolutely have to restock on at my local @hmartofficial . What would you try from this box?

Thank you @atcenterla for gifting me with such a yummy box of all my favorite snacks! If you‚Äôd like to try these out for FREE, definitely make sure to give @atcenterla a follow and register for a box on their website! #gifted

Now the party don‚Äôt start ‚Äòtil @sugarbloomcorner walks in üé∂

SO unbelievably impressed with this beautiful (and yummy) Hawaiian-themed table for a friend‚Äôs birthday. I‚Äôve been a bit hesitant to attend or coordinate social events because of the recent uptick in COVID, so I was especially thankful for how COVID-safe, friendly and efficient the team from @sugarbloomcorner was, and how quickly they put me at ease, both in person and when planning for this over Instagram DM! 

Also wanted to point out that these beautiful pineapple and pina colada cupcakes, mango mousse, mango cheesecake bites and coconut cake were all meticulously baked and decorated by the super talented 13 year old @daysydesserts . I‚Äôve had the honor of trying his treats a few months before, but these honestly blew me away again, especially with how authentic and fresh the mango-flavored mousse and cheesecake bites were! Which treat are you grabbing from this table? üòã

Thank you to @sugarbloomcorner and @daysydesserts for the most party-pleasing setup ever! If you‚Äôre located in the Bay Area, definitely make sure to check out and support both of these local, small, and AAPI-owned businesses for all of your party-related needs! #gifted

Not to be CORNY, but I‚Äôm so glad these @bohemiyum popcorn snacks POPPED into my life!

I‚Äôm typically not a big fan of popcorn, but I loved how these snacks were so light and airy in terms of both flavor and texture. Each snack is certified Kosher, Whole Grain, Vegan (Salt flavor only), Gluten Free, All Organic and uses only non-GMO corn. Best of all, proceeds from every bag sold are donated to art programs in public schools! 

Thank you @bohemiyum for sending me the pink Himalayan salt, sweet brown butter, and lemon zest flavors to try! My favorite was definitely the sweet brown butter, which was so perfectly sweetened, without any hint of grease. Which flavor would you try? #gifted #bohemiyum

Nothing is more TARO-fic than a refreshing cup (or 2 üëÄ) of boba on a hot day! 

Finally got to check out the hype about @tigerteaandjuice , and I was definitely impressed with how deeply flavorful and high quality their drinks are! Here‚Äôs what I got to try:

‚ú® taro milk tea (with sea salt cream add-on): I‚Äôm typically hesitant to get taro at most boba shops (although it‚Äôs one of my favorite milk tea flavors), but I decided to go out on a limb here, and I‚Äôm so glad I did! They use real taro paste, which melds perfectly with the fresh milk when you mix it together! Definitely recommend if you‚Äôre looking for a non-caffeinated beverage. 

‚ú® brown sugar boba milk tea (with potted plant add-on): definitely a solid option for a drink that you can‚Äôt go wrong with! I loved how this drink was not overly sweet and had such a prevalent brown sugar flavor, even when I didn‚Äôt bump down the sweetness! 

‚ú® matcha latte (with potted plant add-on): Would highly recommend adding the potted plant, as it gives this drink a lot more dimension and sweetness, while still maintaining a definite taste of matcha. 

Thank you @tigerteaandjuice for inviting me to try out these drinks! Make sure to check them out at their SJ location- you definitely won‚Äôt be disappointed with the quali-TEA of their drinks! #invite

Finally got to try out these unbelie-BUBBLY beautiful drinks from @sana.na19 , and they definitely did not disappoint!

Among a sea of boba shops, @sana.na19 definitely stands out to me with how meticulously and beautifully crafted their beverages are. You can definitely tell that they put a lot of time and effort into making these drinks, which utilize only the freshest and most authentic ingredients (and no powdered or syrup flavorings). My favorite drink was definitely the creme br√ªl√©e (which is my go to flavor), but their fruit teas (especially the passion fruit) are made really well, especially with how they bring out the natural sweetness and aromas of the fruits! 

Thank you @sana.na19 for such a sweet invite to try out some of the BEST drinks that I‚Äôve had, especially in the Bay Area! Definitely make sure to check out their Fremont pop up at the former Hot Love Cafe, and support an AAPI-owned small business! #invite

Life sure is BATTER with cake, especially if it‚Äôs from @cloudsandcreamco !

Throwback to this insanely beautiful vanilla chiffon cake that @cloudsandcreamco baked for @hangryjess_ and I to surprise our friend Tiffany with, featuring her beloved fur baby @pookiebigears_ ü•∫

Trust me when I say the inside of the cake is as beautiful and delicious as it looks on the outside! The cake was so light and fluffy that it had me floating on CLOUD nine, and the fresh berries and vanilla buttercream added the most subtle and perfect touch of sweetness.

Definitely make sure to check out and support @cloudsandcreamco , an AAPI and woman-owned business! Your eyes and your stomach definitely won‚Äôt regret ordering one of her beautiful and decadent creations (and truthfully one of the BEST cakes that I‚Äôve ever tried!). Would you give this a try? ü•∞

It may be the summer right now, but (THA)I am always craving a hot noodle soup. Here, I‚Äôve whipped up my own version of a spicy tom yum seafood noodle soup using the Tom yum packet from @noodlezero .

Spilling the deetz on how you can score this PHO-nomenal FEAST for yourself! Introducing @clubfeast , a food delivery app where you can schedule meals from your favorite local restaurants for ONLY $6.99 per meal + delivery for $0.49-$2.50 (and at no additional charge to the restaurant)! Make sure to use my code ‚Äúlucia2‚Äù for $20 off (basically three free meals)! Thank you @cravve_app and @clubfeast for setting this up! #collab

Now onto the review- I was honestly so blown away by how amazing this meal was from @phonomenal_asianfusion , especially for the quality and portion size I received! This is definitely one of my new favorite Asian comfort food restaurants in SJ, and I highly recommend checking them out if you‚Äôre looking to get a REALLY good meal and the bang out of your buck!

Garlic noodles - Thought this dish was a bit misleading on how it was advertised- personally, I found it more of a chow mein dish as it barely had any garlic flavor. Nevertheless, it is made really well, and they give you SO many toppings!

Pad Thai - Loved how authentic, fresh and loaded this dish was! FYI it does come already with added spice and a really good amount of shrimp, eggs and tofu- no need to request to add these toppings on as extras!
